content: JERUSALEM, May 7 (Reuters) - Israel on Sunday handed over to Jordan a member of the Jordanian parliament who had been held on suspicion of trying to smuggle weapons into the occupied West Bank, Israel's Shin Bet intelligence agency said.

Shin Bet said that Imad al Adwan, who was detained on April 22 after being arrested at an Israeli-controlled border crossing, was handed over to Jordanian security authorities who will continue investigating the case. (Reporting by Ari Rabinovitch Editing by Steven Scheer)
